quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The foreach Loop[/h1]

The [b]foreach [/b]loop works only on arrays, and is used to loop through each key/value pair in an array.

There are two syntaxes: [code format="php" ][b]foreach [/b](array as $value) {
  code to be executed;
}
//or
[b]foreach [/b](array as $key => $value) {
   code to be executed;
}[/code]
The first form loops over the array. On each iteration, the value of the current element is assigned to [b]$value[/b], and the array pointer is moved by one, until it reaches the last array element.
The second form will additionally assign the current element's key to the [b]$key[/b] variable on each iteration.

The following example demonstrates a loop that outputs the values of the [b]$names[/b] array.[code format="php" codeId="481"]$names = array("John", "David", "Amy");
[b]foreach[/b] ($names [b]as[/b] $name) {
   echo $name.'<br />';
}

// John
// David
// Amy[/code]
